      • getTestCaseWithRevision

        IWorkItem getTestCaseWithRevision()
        Returns:
        Test case with revision if the revision is set. If not, returns the test case without revision.

      • setTestCaseWithRevision

        void setTestCaseWithRevision(IWorkItem testCase)
        This is the method which must be used by clients to set the test case for this record. Test record stores also the current revision of the work item (or baseline) to indicate the exact state of the test case. Useful for setting executed (done) test cases.

      • setTestCase

        void setTestCase(IWorkItem testCase)
        Set the test case without revision, i. e. it should be always taken from HEAD. Useful for planning of test cases. When this method is called in baseline or with test case from revision it does the same like setTestCaseWithRevision(IWorkItem).
        Since:
        3.6.2

      • setResult

        void setResult(@Nullable

        Sets the test result and, if required by the test run, signs the execution by current user. Note that signing of a test record execution is allowed only via Polarion UI.

      • setResult

      • getAttachments

        @NotNull
java.util.List<ITestRunAttachment> getAttachments()
        Returns list of attachments of this test record.

        Returned list will NOT contain attachments attached to the test step results - those are accessible via ITestStepResult.getAttachments().

        Since:
        3.7.3

      • isPaused

        boolean isPaused()
        Checks if this test record is in paused state. Paused means, that related test case was partially executed (some data like test step results, attachments,... was filled), but has no result (test case verdict) yet. If test record is neither isPaused() nor isPlanned() then related test case was fully executed.
        Since:
        3.9.2

      • isPlanned

        boolean isPlanned()
        Checks if this test record is in planned state. Planned means, that related test case wasn't executed (even partially) and has no result (test case verdict). If test record is neither isPaused() nor isPlanned() then related test case was fully executed.
        Since:
        3.9.2

      • isExecuted

        boolean isExecuted()
        Checks if the related test case was fully executed (i.e. if it is neither isPaused() nor isPlanned()).
        Since:
        3.9.2

      • getIteration

        int getIteration()
        If there are multiple test records for a single test case, these test records are also called iterations. The iteration number of a test record is the index of it in the list of all test records for the same test case in the containing test run.
        Returns:
        test iteration number or -1 if test record is newly created.
        Since:
        3.9.2

      • isIteration

        boolean isIteration()
        Returns:
        true if there are multiple test records for same test case, otherwise it returns false.
        Since:
        3.9.2
        See Also:
        getIteration()

      • isSigned

        boolean isSigned()
        Returns:
        true if this test record is executed and electronically signed
        Since:
        3.10.0
